MPEG-2 allows stuffing to be done in several places:

Transport packet stuffing is at the end of its adaptation field.
This is done by specifying a adaptation_field_length which is larger
than the actual size of the adaptation field.  Stuffing byte value is 0xFF.

PES packet stuffing is at the end of the PES header.  This is done by
specifying a PES_header_data_length value which is larger than the
actual size of the PES optional header.  Stuffing byte value is 0xFF.
There should be no more than 32 stuffing bytes in a PES packet.

Note: both TP and PES level stuffing is done at the end of the header,
      right before the payload.

Video layer stuffing is at the end of a coded picture.  This is done by
inserting extra 0x00 bytes before the next (sequence, GOP, or picture)
start code.  Buffering in video layer affect the picture size and VBV buffer
fullness.
